snippet.textDisplay: All time fav coke studio songs for sure. Killer fusion. Superb arrangement, bass, both vocals 👏👌 But I do want to mention an aspect of this song that doesn't get enough attention perhaps -- the lyrics of this song! Boy do they really get me each time. There's a certain existential angst expressed in this song which doesn't deflate but makes one connect with "the larger picture". Manoj Yadav is the lyricist if I have that right. Love this song and all of its elements ❤️
snippet.textOriginal: All time fav coke studio songs for sure. Killer fusion. snippet.textDisplay:
This is one of the finest of CokeStudio India. Clinton shines in composition, arrangement. He always amazes me with his musical prowess. While not strictly from a Indian Classical bground, the way he has composed keeping the classical and progressive rock elements here, its incredible. The main riff of the song so groovy. Always a huge fan of Nandini. Highly underrated singer. Also, the vocal arrangement (the bground vocals, harmony) is so effective. One thing I have always maintained, there are two people in the entire country, who are the vocals arrangement extraordinaire, Clinton and Nandini (listen to her album, Beete Pal). We are fortunate to have both in here.
This song is certainly in my top10 MTV Coke Studio hall of fame!
